    "created_at": "2016-02-27T21:36:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-27T21:38:07Z",
    "body": "Actually, in my usecase, I think I need a server... \n- I am uploading the artifacts (RELEASES, .nupkg, .exe) on Github.\n- AutoUpdater does not have an interface to Github, so I used a third-party server called [nuts](https://github.com/gitbookio/nuts) to provide my app with the requested asset URL to download. Now I need to run this server somewhere, so I thought maybe localhost _can_ work.\n- When this failed, I tried with a small go server I wrote myself, which basically just serves the `.exe` from the latest release\n- In both cases, `checkForUpdates` fails even before it pings the `/update_check` route.\n\nShort of hosting a separate server, is there anyway I can make this work?\n"
  },
